data.name: Spicy Jalapeño Burger
data.quickTastyDescription: A mouthwatering burger with a spicy kick from fresh jalapeños, complemented by creamy avocado and zesty chipotle mayo, perfect for spice lovers!
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat a grill or skillet over medium-high heat.
In a bowl, season the ground beef with salt and pepper, then form into 4 patties.
Drizzle olive oil on the grill or skillet, and cook the patties for about 3-4 minutes on one side.
Flip the patties and add a slice of cheddar cheese on top. Cook for another 3-4 minutes for medium doneness.
While the burgers are cooking, lightly toast the burger buns on the grill or skillet until golden brown.
Assemble the burgers by spreading chipotle mayo on the bottom bun, then add lettuce, a burger patty, jalapeño slices, avocado, and tomato.
Top with the other half of the bun and serve hot.
data.modifiersForBase: Spicy with jalapeños and chipotle mayo
